<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="143" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,858,1227,1252]" box="[151,858,1227,1252]" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">
<typeStatus box="[151,201,1228,1252]" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">Type</typeStatus>
species: 
<taxonomicName authority="Alekseev &amp; Bukejs, 2021" authorityName="Alekseev &amp; Bukejs" authorityYear="2021" box="[294,593,1227,1251]" class="Insecta" family="Melandryidae" genus="Electroxylita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chronographica" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[294,593,1227,1251]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">Electroxylita chronographica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[599,680,1227,1251]" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[599,680,1227,1251]" pageId="1" pageNumber="143" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, here designated.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1297,2008]" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,214,1297,1323]" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">Note.</emphasis>
The newly described fossil taxon, 
<taxonomicName authority="Alekseev &amp; Bukejs, 2021" authorityName="Alekseev &amp; Bukejs" authorityYear="2021" box="[597,741,1297,1323]" class="Insecta" family="Melandryidae" genus="Electroxylita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[597,741,1297,1323]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">Electroxylita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[746,850,1297,1323]" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[746,850,1297,1323]" pageId="1" pageNumber="143" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, possesses typical external morphological characters of the tribe 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1864" box="[278,365,1333,1359]" class="Insecta" family="Melandryidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Xylitini">Xylitini</taxonomicName>
within the subfamily 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1815" box="[607,767,1333,1359]" class="Insecta" family="Melandryidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Melandryinae">Melandryinae</taxonomicName>
: procoxae contiguous, pretarsal claws simple, 11-segmented antennae short and filiform, base of pronotum closely associated with elytral base, head concealed from above, lateral and basal edges of pronotum margined, lateral pronotal sides carinate, pronotum without impressions at base, notosternal sutures distinct but non-carinate, penultimate tarsomere of pro- and mesotarsi widened, meso- and metatibial spurs equal in lengths and comparatively short, tibiae without ridges, protrochantin visible, metatarsomere 1 long etc. However, 
<taxonomicName authority="Alekseev &amp; Bukejs, 2021" authorityName="Alekseev &amp; Bukejs" authorityYear="2021" box="[461,605,1513,1539]" class="Insecta" family="Melandryidae" genus="Electroxylita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[461,605,1513,1539]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">Electroxylita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[613,719,1513,1539]" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[613,719,1513,1539]" pageId="1" pageNumber="143" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
does not fully correspond to any extant genus of the tribe, and therefore it is placed into a new genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="144" pageId="1" pageNumber="143" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1297,2008]" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,461,1585,1611]" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
The tribe 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1864" box="[573,663,1585,1611]" class="Insecta" family="Melandryidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Xylitini">Xylitini</taxonomicName>
, consists of 5–6 extant genera (
<bibRefCitation author="Nikitsky, N. B. &amp; Pollock, D. A." box="[1007,1291,1585,1611]" pageId="1" pageNumber="143" refId="ref16460" refString="Nikitsky, N. B. &amp; Pollock, D. A. (2010) Melandryidae. In: Leschen, R. A. B., Beutel, R. G. &amp; Lawrence, J. F. (Eds.), Handbook of Zoology. Vol. 2. Coleoptera, Beetles. Morphology and Systematics (Elateroidea, Bostrichiformia, Cucujiformia partim). Walter de Gruyter GmbH &amp; Co, Berlin, pp. 520 - 533." type="book" year="2010">Nikitsky &amp; Pollock 2010</bibRefCitation>
), namely 
<taxonomicName authority="Paykull, 1798" authorityName="Paykull" authorityYear="1798" class="Insecta" family="Melandryidae" genus="Xylita" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">Xylita</emphasis>
Paykull, 1798
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Forel, 1893" authorityName="Forel" authorityYear="1893" box="[366,583,1621,1647]" class="Insecta" family="Melandryidae" genus="Rushia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[366,444,1621,1647]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">Rushia</emphasis>
Förel, 1893
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Jacquelin du Val, 1863" authorityName="Jacquelin du Val" authorityYear="1863" box="[594,984,1621,1647]" class="Insecta" family="Melandryidae" genus="Dolotarsus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[594,718,1621,1647]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">Dolotarsus</emphasis>
Jacquelin du Val, 1863
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="LeConte, 1874" authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1874" box="[995,1296,1621,1647]" class="Insecta" family="Melandryidae" genus="Scotochroa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[995,1122,1621,1647]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">Scotochroa</emphasis>
LeConte, 1874
</taxonomicName>
(which may be synonymous with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jacquelin du Val" authorityYear="1863" box="[391,515,1657,1683]" class="Insecta" family="Melandryidae" genus="Dolotarsus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[391,515,1657,1683]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">Dolotarsus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), 
<taxonomicName authority="Mank, 1939" authorityName="Mank" authorityYear="1939" box="[539,842,1657,1683]" class="Insecta" family="Melandryidae" genus="Scotochroides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[539,697,1657,1683]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">Scotochroides</emphasis>
Mank, 1939
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="LeConte, 1862" authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1862" box="[901,1169,1657,1683]" class="Insecta" family="Melandryidae" genus="Spilotus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[901,991,1657,1683]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">Spilotus</emphasis>
LeConte, 1862
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Alekseev &amp; Bukejs, 2021" authorityName="Alekseev &amp; Bukejs" authorityYear="2021" box="[1180,1324,1657,1683]" class="Insecta" family="Melandryidae" genus="Electroxylita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1180,1324,1657,1683]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">Electroxylita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1331,1436,1657,1683]" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1331,1436,1657,1683]" pageId="1" pageNumber="143" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Paykull" authorityYear="1798" box="[295,362,1693,1719]" class="Insecta" family="Melandryidae" genus="Xylita" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[295,362,1693,1719]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">Xylita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Forel" authorityYear="1893" box="[377,455,1693,1719]" class="Insecta" family="Melandryidae" genus="Rushia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[377,455,1693,1719]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">Rushia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jacquelin du Val" authorityYear="1863" box="[470,594,1693,1719]" class="Insecta" family="Melandryidae" genus="Dolotarsus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[470,594,1693,1719]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">Dolotarsus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1874" box="[658,785,1693,1719]" class="Insecta" family="Melandryidae" genus="Scotochroa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[658,785,1693,1719]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">Scotochroa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in conical antennomeres distinctly longer than wide. The newly described genus can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Forel" authorityYear="1893" box="[718,796,1729,1755]" class="Insecta" family="Melandryidae" genus="Rushia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[718,796,1729,1755]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">Rushia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1862" box="[810,900,1729,1755]" class="Insecta" family="Melandryidae" genus="Spilotus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[810,900,1729,1755]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">Spilotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Paykull" authorityYear="1798" box="[964,1031,1729,1755]" class="Insecta" family="Melandryidae" genus="Xylita" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[964,1031,1729,1755]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">Xylita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the comparatively short prosternum before proxocal cavities, from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Forel" authorityYear="1893" box="[554,632,1765,1791]" class="Insecta" family="Melandryidae" genus="Rushia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[554,632,1765,1791]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">Rushia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the anteriorly converging lateral pronotal margins, from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1874" box="[1310,1437,1765,1791]" class="Insecta" family="Melandryidae" genus="Scotochroa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1310,1437,1765,1791]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">Scotochroa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the shape of apical maxillary palpomere, from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Paykull" authorityYear="1798" box="[711,778,1801,1827]" class="Insecta" family="Melandryidae" genus="Xylita" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[711,778,1801,1827]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">Xylita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the separate mesocoxae and transverse pronotum, from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mank" authorityYear="1939" box="[151,309,1837,1863]" class="Insecta" family="Melandryidae" genus="Scotochroides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,309,1837,1863]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">Scotochroides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by shorter and not so robust antennae, from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1862" box="[803,893,1837,1863]" class="Insecta" family="Melandryidae" genus="Spilotus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[803,893,1837,1863]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">Spilotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in procoxal cavities with distinct fissure, unicolorous elytra, and weakly bisinuate pronotal base.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1297,2008]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1437,151,609]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="144" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">
The oldest geological record of the family 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1815" box="[671,827,1909,1935]" class="Insecta" family="Melandryidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Melandryidae</taxonomicName>
is 
<taxonomicName authority="Nikitsky 1977" authorityName="Nikitsky" authorityYear="1977" box="[858,1296,1909,1935]" class="Insecta" family="Melandryidae" genus="Archaeoxylita" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zherichini">
<emphasis box="[858,1132,1909,1935]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">Archaeoxylita zherichini</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Nikitsky, N. B." box="[1138,1296,1909,1935]" pageId="1" pageNumber="143" pagination="140 - 143" refId="ref16201" refString="Nikitsky, N. B. (1977) Two new genera of false darkling beetles (Coleoptera, Melandryidae) from Upper Cretaceous. Paleontological Journal, 2, 140 - 143. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1977">Nikitsky 1977</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from Lower Cretaceous (Santonian) Taimyr amber (
<bibRefCitation author="Nikitsky, N. B." box="[589,754,1945,1971]" pageId="1" pageNumber="143" pagination="140 - 143" refId="ref16201" refString="Nikitsky, N. B. (1977) Two new genera of false darkling beetles (Coleoptera, Melandryidae) from Upper Cretaceous. Paleontological Journal, 2, 140 - 143. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1977">Nikitsky 1977</bibRefCitation>
). The original description of 
<taxonomicName box="[1076,1232,1945,1971]" class="Insecta" family="Melandryidae" genus="Archaeoxylita" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1076,1232,1945,1971]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="143">Archaeoxylita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
lacks tribal placement, but the genus corresponds to the tribe 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1864" box="[654,741,1981,2007]" class="Insecta" family="Melandryidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Xylitini">Xylitini</taxonomicName>
in reported characters (procoxae contiguous, penultimate tarsomere widened, large and cultriform ultimate maxillary palpomere, non-striate elytra etc.). The Cretaceous beetle resembles the recent genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Forel" authorityYear="1893" box="[465,543,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Melandryidae" genus="Rushia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="144" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[465,543,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="144">Rushia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and strongly resembles 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Paykull" authorityYear="1798" box="[822,889,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Melandryidae" genus="Xylita" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="144" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[822,889,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="144">Xylita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
according to original diagnosis and comparison (
<bibRefCitation author="Nikitsky, N. B." box="[159,326,223,249]" pageId="2" pageNumber="144" pagination="140 - 143" refId="ref16201" refString="Nikitsky, N. B. (1977) Two new genera of false darkling beetles (Coleoptera, Melandryidae) from Upper Cretaceous. Paleontological Journal, 2, 140 - 143. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1977">Nikitsky 1977</bibRefCitation>
). The Baltic amber 
<taxonomicName authority="Alekseev &amp; Bukejs, 2021" authorityName="Alekseev &amp; Bukejs" authorityYear="2021" box="[556,700,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Melandryidae" genus="Electroxylita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="144" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[556,700,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="144">Electroxylita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[709,817,223,249]" pageId="2" pageNumber="144">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[709,817,223,249]" pageId="2" pageNumber="144" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[972,1128,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Melandryidae" genus="Archaeoxylita" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="144" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[972,1128,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="144">Archaeoxylita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in relative length ratios of metatarsomeres, in comparatively non-widened antennomeres 9 and 10, in larger body size (body length of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nikitsky" authorityYear="1977" class="Insecta" family="Melandryidae" genus="Archaeoxylita" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="144" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zherichini">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="144">Archaeoxylita zherichini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is about 
<quantity box="[448,517,295,321]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="144" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,609]" pageId="2" pageNumber="144">
Additionally, 
<taxonomicName authority="Alekseev &amp; Bukejs, 2021" authorityName="Alekseev &amp; Bukejs" authorityYear="2021" box="[353,497,331,357]" class="Insecta" family="Melandryidae" genus="Electroxylita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="144" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[353,497,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="144">Electroxylita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[505,610,331,357]" pageId="2" pageNumber="144">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[505,610,331,357]" pageId="2" pageNumber="144" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
differs from extant representatives of the tribe in the following combination of characters: (1) small body size (extant representatives are mostly larger than 
<quantity box="[1097,1167,367,393]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="144" unit="mm" value="6.0">6 mm</quantity>
), (2) large apical maxillary palpomere (longer than palpomeres 1–3 combined), (3) short portion of prosternum before procoxae; and (4) uniform and very fine pronotal and elytral punctuation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="144" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,609]" pageId="2" pageNumber="144">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,475,501]" pageId="2" pageNumber="144">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name of the new genus is a compound word: “electron” (ancient Greek word for amber), and “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Paykull" authorityYear="1798" box="[164,231,511,537]" class="Insecta" family="Melandryidae" genus="Xylita" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="144" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[164,231,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="144">Xylita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” (name of the 
<typeStatus box="[398,446,511,537]" pageId="2" pageNumber="144">type</typeStatus>
genus in the tribe). The gender is feminine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="144" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,609]" pageId="2" pageNumber="144">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,547,573]" pageId="2" pageNumber="144">Remarks.</emphasis>
The new genus is monotypic, represented by the 
<typeStatus box="[859,907,547,573]" pageId="2" pageNumber="144">type</typeStatus>
species only. Therefore, the generic description considerably overlaps that of the species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
